Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Cook apples, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons granulated sugar in saucepan on medium heat 6 minutes or until apples are tender, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Mix flour, brown sugar, oats and half the butter until blended; spread onto rimmed baking sheet. Bake 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Meanwhile, mix graham crumbs and remaining butter; press onto bottom of 9-inch springform pan. Top with apple mixture, spreading to within 1/2 inch of edge. Beat cream cheese, remaining granulated sugar and vanilla with mixer until blended. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each just until blended; pour over apple mixture. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until centre is almost set. Run knife around rim of pan to loosen cake; cool before removing rim. Refrigerate cheesecake 4 hours. Top with streusel and caramel sauce just before serving.